mit\nor that the objects are dormant. Only one Centaur in our sample -- 2014\nPQ$_{70}$ experienced a sudden decrease in semi-major axis and perihelion\ndistance attributed to the onset of activity for some previously known inactive\nCentaurs, and therefore is a likely candidate for future outburst. This object\nshould be a target of interest for further observational monitoring.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Jul 2021 01:26:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-30"}
